## 2. Framework Selection

### Decision Tree

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Choose Framework] --> B{Need SEO?}
    B -->|Yes| C{Need Dynamic Content?}
    C -->|Yes| D[Next.js]
    C -->|No| E[Static Site Generator]
    B -->|No| F{Single Page App?}
    F -->|Yes| G[React or Vue]
    F -->|No| H[Legacy or MPA]
    D --> I{TypeScript Required?}
    I -->|Yes| J[Use TypeScript]
    I -->|No| K[TypeScript Recommended]
```

### Framework Options

| Framework           | Use When                              | Skip When              |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| **Next.js**         | SEO needed, full-stack web app        | Simple static site     |
| **Remix**           | Full-stack, data-heavy                | Need granular control  |
| **Astro**           | Content-focused, islands architecture | App-like interactivity |
| **Express/Fastify** | API-only backend                      | Need full framework    |
| **React**           | SPA, no SSR needed                    | SEO is priority        |
| **Vue**             | Team prefers Vue syntax               | Team prefers React     |

### Recommended Next.js Init Command

```bash
npx create-next-app@latest my-project \
  --typescript \
  --tailwind \
  --eslint \
  --app \
  --src-dir \
  --import-alias "@/*" \
  --use-pnpm \
  --yes
```

