## 3. Authentication Decision

### Decision Tree

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Authentication] --> B{Need Auth?}
    B -->|No Auth| C[Skip to next step]
    B -->|Yes| D{Complexity Level?}
    D -->|Simple| E[Auth.js / NextAuth]
    D -->|Complex| F[Custom + Database]
    D -->|Enterprise| G[Clerk / Auth0]
    E --> H{Provider?}
    H -->|Social Only| I[Firebase Auth]
    H -->|Email/Password| J[Supabase Auth]
    H -->|Multi-provider| K[Auth.js]
```

### Auth Options by Use Case

| Scenario               | Recommended        | Alternative   |
| ---------------------- | ------------------ | ------------- |
| **Simple, fast setup** | Firebase Auth      | Supabase Auth |
| **Need custom logic**  | Auth.js (NextAuth) | Custom JWT    |
| **Enterprise, SSO**    | Clerk              | Auth0         |
| **No auth needed**     | Skip entirely      | -             |

### Auth Implementation Patterns

#### Option A: Firebase Auth (Simple)

```typescript
// lib/firebase.ts
import { initializeApp } from "firebase/app";
import { getAuth } from "firebase/auth";

const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY,
  // ... other config
};

const app = initializeApp(firebaseConfig);
export const auth = getAuth(app);
```

#### Option B: Auth.js (Next.js)

```bash
pnpm add next-auth
```

```typescript
// app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts
import NextAuth from "next-auth";
import GoogleProvider from "next-auth/providers/google";

const handler = NextAuth({
  providers: [
    GoogleProvider({
      clientId: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID!,
      clientSecret: process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET!,
    }),
  ],
});

export { handler as GET, handler as POST };
```

