## 4. Database & Backend

### Decision Tree

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Database] --> B{Need Database?}
    B -->|No| C[Skip - Static/Client-only]
    B -->|Yes| D{Data Structure?}
    D -->|Relational| E[PostgreSQL]
    D -->|Document| F[Firestore / MongoDB]
    D -->|Key-Value| G[Redis]
    D -->|Graph| H[Neo4j]
    E --> I{Managed or Self-hosted?}
    I -->|Managed| J[Supabase / Neon]
    I -->|Self-hosted| K[Docker + Railway]
```

### Database Options

| Database       | Use When                                            | Skip When             |
| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| **Firestore**  | Real-time, document structure, Firebase ecosystem   | Complex relationships |
| **Supabase**   | PostgreSQL + REST/Realtime, open source alternative | Need GraphQL          |
| **MongoDB**    | Flexible schema, rapid prototyping                  | Strict ACID needed    |
| **PostgreSQL** | Complex queries, relations, migrations              | Simple key-value only |
| **Redis**      | Caching, sessions, rate limiting                    | Primary data store    |

### Backend Pattern

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Frontend] --> B[API Routes / Server Actions]
    B --> C{Database?}
    C -->|Yes| D[Database Client]
    C -->|No| E[Return Data]
```

#### Next.js API Route Pattern

```typescript
// app/api/resource/route.ts
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  // Validate auth
  // Query database
  // Return response
}

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  // Validate input
  // Transform data
  // Save to database
  // Return result
}
```

